<HEADLINE>
<P>
SHIRLEY MAXWELL; RETIRED LAPD SERGEANT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Shirley Maxwell, 68, a retired Los Angeles Police Department sergeant who was 
one of the first women to attain that rank. She also was the first policewoman 
to receive an award from the Christians and Jews for Law and Morality. Mrs. 
Maxwell, who was married to an LAPD detective, worked primarily on juvenile 
cases during her 26 years with the department. Her basic assignments were in 
the West Los Angeles area. She retired in 1969. In Inglewood on June 2 of 
cancer. 
</P>
