<HEADLINE>
<P>
MISL CHAMPIONSHIP SERIES; 
</P>
<P>
BALTIMORE BLANKS SOCKERS, 7-0 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By AP 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BALTIMORE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Goalkeeper Scott Manning recorded his third career shutout as the Baltimore 
Blast pushed the Major Indoor Soccer League Championship Series to a decisive 
seventh game with a 7-0 victory over the San Diego Sockers Thursday night. 
</P>
<P>
Manning made nine saves as the Blast, who once trailed, three games to one, 
evened the series at 3-3. 
</P>
<P>
The final game will be played Saturday at the Baltimore Arena. 
</P>
<P>
Manning's shutout was the third in championship series history and the first 
since 1983, when San Diego goalkeeper Alan Mayer posted consecutive shutouts 
against Baltimore. 
</P>
<P>
David Byrne provided all the offensive firepower the Blast needed, scoring two 
goals and assisting on four others. 
</P>
<P>
Rusty Troy, Freddie Thompson, Carl Valentine, Billy Ronson and Stan Koziol 
scored single goals for the Blast. 
</P>
<P>
Manning's shutout was his second with Baltimore. 
</P>
</TEXT>
