<P>
MORNING REPORT: MOVIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALEENE MacMINN, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
John Bailey has been replaced by award-winning documentary maker Richard Pearce 
as director of a civil rights film starring Sissy Spacek and Whoopi Goldberg 
that is being shot in Montgomery, Ala. "The Long Walk Home" was to be Bailey's 
directorial debut, but that was derailed by "creative differences," according 
to a spokesman for the film."The Long Walk Home" is being financed by 
independent film producer New Visions Pictures with a budget of about $6 
million. ALEENE MacMINN 
