<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jarvis Jovan Clark, 28, of San Diego was arrested about 8 p.m. Wednesday in 
connection with the shooting death of Andra Lasar Williams, 22, and the 
wounding of Torrance Nunn, 29, about 90 minutes earlier, according to Sgt. Hank 
Olais. 
</P>
<P>
Police answered a call about 6:30 p.m. at the Harbor Villa apartment complex on 
17th Street near Imperial Avenue and found Williams lying on a third-floor 
landing. 
</P>
<P>
Williams died of multiple gunshot wounds, Deputy Coroner Max Murphy said. Nunn 
was struck once in the left thigh and was taken to UC San Diego Medical Center. 
He was listed in fair condition Thursday, hospital spokeswoman Sheri Smith 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Nunn had been released earlier Wednesday for treatment of burns, Smith said. 
</P>
<P>
Olais said Clark began firing at Nunn and Williams with a high-powered 
automatic weapon after an argument. Clark then drove off in a car with a woman, 
Olais said. 
</P>
<P>
Police saw the car a short while later at Euclid and Imperial avenues and 
questioned the occupants, who directed officers to an Imperial Avenue hair 
salon. 
</P>
<P>
Clark was inquiring about hairdos when police arrived and he was arrested, 
Olais said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
