<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN MARCOS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Valley Center man was killed Wednesday when he lost control of the truck he 
was driving and was thrown from the vehicle when it overturned, Deputy Coroner 
Max Murphy said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
Terry Lynn Leopard, 36, of Vesper Road in Valley Center, was believed to have 
been speeding on Elfin Forest Road near Questhaven Road in San Marcos when he 
lost control and overturned about 6:30 p.m., Murphy said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
