<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: 2 TEEN-AGERS HELD IN SLAYING OF GIRL, 15 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A teen-age gang member and a 16-year-old female companion have been arrested in 
the shooting death of a 15-year-old girl who had just gotten out of the 
suspect's car on a Mid-City street, Los Angeles police said. 
</P>
<P>
Kim Cater, 15, was shot and killed about 12:40 a.m. Tuesday on Arlington 
Avenue, Detective Paul Mize said. 
</P>
<P>
Cater and a girlfriend had just gotten out of a car at Arlington Avenue and 
25th Street and had walked about a block and a half when the driver of the car 
pulled up, got out and fired at least three shots, Mize said. 
</P>
<P>
Cater died at the scene. Her friend was not injured, he said. "We're 
investigating this as a gang-related shooting," Mize said. 
</P>
<P>
Later Tuesday, police arrested and booked Olyric Robinson, 18, a known gang 
member, on suspicion of murder. 
</P>
