<P>
McCaw Wants Lin to Halt TV Spinoff: McCaw Cellular Communications, which 
announced this week that it is bidding $6.5 billion for Lin Broadcasting, said 
the offer for its rival was conditioned on Lin halting its planned spinoff of 
seven broadcast television stations. In a filing with the Securities and 
Exchange Commission, McCaw, the nation's largest cellular telephone company, 
said the spinoff would "materially reduce the value of the company's common 
stock outstanding" and incur substantial costs. If Lin carries out the planned 
spinoff, McCaw said it would either reduce its $120-a-share offer for the 
broadcasting and cellular communications company or withdraw it altogether. 
