<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Allegheny Denied Extension: A U. S. bankruptcy court judge has denied a request 
by Allegheny International to extend for six weeks its exclusive right to plan 
its reorganization under Chapter 11 bankruptcy laws. The judge's decision 
clears the way for the appliance maker's creditors to file their own 
reorganization plans, which could include proposals to sell all or part of the 
company. The extension would have been Allegheny's 10th since filing for 
protection from creditors in February, 1988; the latest period expired June 2. 
"There's almost a disease abroad," said Judge Joseph Cosetti, announcing his 
decision. "When you don't know what to do, you delay." 
</P>
</TEXT>
