<P>
U.S. BLAMED IN FLOW OF REFUGEES TO HONG KONG 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
HONG KONG 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The United States is partly to blame for a huge influx of Vietnamese "boat 
people" into Hong Kong, a relief official said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
Chris Bale, Hong Kong director of the British-based charity organization Oxfam, 
said Washington has applied pressure on Southeast Asian nations to provide 
asylum to boat people fleeing Vietnam. 
</P>
