<HEADLINE>
<P>
BALD EAGLE BANDIT MAY HAVE WINGS TRIMMED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A man suspected of being the county's most prolific bank robber, dubbed the 
Bald Eagle by authorities, was arrested Thursday at a bar in Anaheim. 
</P>
<P>
Buena Park police arrested Hector Rodrigo Soto, 31, of Yorba Linda on suspicion 
of 16 bank robberies committed since Jan. 4. Twelve of those were in Orange 
County, the other four in Los Angeles County. 
</P>
<P>
Officer Richard McMillan said the department's undercover unit received 
information from the FBI on Tuesday about places that Soto frequents. 
Undercover officers arrested Soto in the bar on Euclid Avenue without incident. 
</P>
<P>
The robber was known for his bald pate and thick, metal-rim glasses. He usually 
carried a briefcase and, on occasion, impatiently reached over the bank counter 
to grab money from a cash drawer, the FBI said. 
</P>
<P>
He had been seen leaving bank robberies in a brown compact car with the license 
619 SND. 
</P>
<P>
Soto is held in Orange County Jail without bail. 
</P>
</TEXT>
