<HEADLINE>
<P>
ON THE BEACHES; 
</P>
<P>
RIDING TO THE WAVES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Clipboard researched by Rick VanderKnyff / Los Angeles Times; Graphics by 
Doris Shields / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Especially for the younger set, summer means taking the bus to the beach. Below 
are 15 OCTD bus routes that take landlocked residents of inland Orange County 
to sun, sand and surf. Major stops are listed; buses arrive approximately every 
20 minutes during the week and every half-hour on weekends. Daily times for 
first and last runs vary; call for specific schedule information. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
INFORMATION: (714) 636-RIDE. 
</P>
<P>
FARES: 80 cents (85 cents beginning July 1). Exact change required. 
</P>
<P>
SURFBOARDS: Only those less than 6 feet allowed on buses. 
</P>
<P>
MOST POPULAR ROUTES: 29, 35, 43, 53 and 91. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
1 Pacific Coast Highway, from Long Beach to Capistrano Beach 
</P>
<P>
STOPS 
</P>
<P>
Long Beach Civic Center 
</P>
<P>
Long Beach Circle 
</P>
<P>
Veterans Administration Hospital 
</P>
<P>
