<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TOKYO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Prime Minister Sosuke Uno today refused to respond as a questioner in 
Parliament broke precedent by asking him about a news report claiming he kept a 
highly paid geisha as his mistress. 
</P>
<P>
Uno, who previously denied the report to journalists, said he would not comment 
on it in a public forum. 
</P>
