The report surfaced last weekend in the Sunday Mainichi magazine. An article 
quoted an unidentified 40-year-old woman as saying Uno had paid her $2,100 a 
month over a four-month period in 1985. "He is not a man of noble character," 
the article quoted the woman as saying. "I don't want him to use politics the 
same way he treated me." 
