<TEXT>
<P>
The Jackson Daily News, one of Mississippi's largest's newspapers, ceased 
publication today in its 98th year. 
</P>
<P>
The Gannett Co. afternoon paper, which has been losing circulation, will merge 
with its sister morning publication, the Clarion-Ledger, Monday. 
</P>
<P>
John Johnson, executive editor of both newspapers, said the merger will 
increase the news staff from about 88 to 116 and there will be no layoffs. 
</P>
<P>
The estimated circulation of the merged newspapers is 102,000 daily. 
